  <h2 id="self-cleaning">Self-Cleaning Solids Ejection</h2>
  <p>
    The DMPX-014&rsquo;s self-cleaning mechanism uses hydraulic pressure to actuate piston ports at the bowl periphery. During a discharge (cleaning shot), the bowl periphery opens momentarily, ejecting accumulated solids as a wet sludge into the solids collection shroud. The entire discharge cycle takes less than one second and the machine immediately resumes full-speed separation.
  </p>
  <p>
    Discharge frequency is programmed through the PLC based on the solids loading of the feed. Applications with heavy solids (waste oil, tank bottoms) typically use discharge intervals of 15&ndash;60 minutes. Low-solids applications (diesel polishing, biodiesel washing) may discharge every few hours. The PLC can also trigger partial discharges to avoid unnecessary dilution of the separated product.
  </p>
  <p>
    Because solids ejection is automatic, the DMPX-014 runs unattended in continuous 24/7 operation without manual cleaning shutdowns &mdash; a key advantage over manual-clean centrifuge designs.
  </p>

